<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="553" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1 Economic Commission/53:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hull</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-19T17:00:00-04:00">July 19,
                                    1933—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>160. Your 149, July 19, 1 a.m. The President authorizes you to make a
                            formal statement along the lines suggested.</p>
                        <p>The British limitation of home-grown sugar is satisfactory, provided that
                            after the first 2 years the permitted increase will be the same as that
                            allowed for the United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>